This paper proposes a method for learning structural node representations in a network, which falls under the category of network analysis and machine learning. The paper focuses on developing a fast and efficient approach for this task, which suggests it may fall under sub-categories such as "Social and Information Networks (cs.SI)", "Machine Learning (cs.LG)", "Sound and Music Computing (cs.SD)", "Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS)", and "Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI)".
